# 1906 Badge of the Colony

## Archival Material

The Badge of the Colony issue is one of the most beautiful issues of Grenada. there exists an artists
drawing showing the design used for the stamps and the issue can be found in trials, essays, proofs and the like.

\ph[50%]{../grenada/405.jpg}{1906 Badge of the Colony large artist's drawing of central vignette, in black ink and Chinese white, on thick wove paper measuring 133x143mm, exceptionally well done in this large size to show the detail of this attractive design, tiny pinhole and a few flecks of toning, otherwise very fine; undoubtedly a unique original drawing from the De La Rue archives Est. 1,500-2,000
SOLD for $1,600.00} 
{{auction:Gross}}




This article is divided into three parts, essays, trials, plate proofs and stamps and covers. They are mostly from the 2003 Ward
sale.

## Die Proofs

The first four low values were printed by the engraved 
method, later higher values were typographed, 
so it is not unusual to find proofs for both methods. die proofs both in black and blue exist and are shown below.


<h4>Die proof in Black</h4>

